(A)

ADJUSTED NET INTEREST INCOME AND NET INTEREST YIELD ON CARD MEMBER LOANS ARE

NON-GAAP

MEASURES. REFER TO GLOSSARY OF SELECTED TERMINOLOGY FOR DEFINITIONS OF THESE

TERMS. WE BELIEVE ADJUSTED NET INTEREST INCOME IS USEFUL TO INVESTORS BECAUSE IT IS A COMPONENT OF NET INTEREST YIELD ON CARD MEMBER LOANS, WHICH PROVIDES A MEASURE OF PROFITABILITY OF OUR CARD MEMBER LOAN PORTFOLIO.

