BASEL III.

SHARE REPURCHASES AND DIVIDENDS

WE RETURN

CAPITAL TO COMMON SHAREHOLDERS THROUGH DIVIDENDS AND SHARE REPURCHASES. THE SHARE REPURCHASES REDUCE COMMON SHARES OUTSTANDING AND MORE THAN OFFSET THE ISSUANCE OF NEW SHARES AS PART OF EMPLOYEE COMPENSATION PLANS.

DURING THE YEAR ENDED DECEMBER 31, 2016, WE RETURNED $5.5 BILLION TO OUR SHAREHOLDERS IN THE FORM OF COMMON STOCK DIVIDENDS ($1.1 BILLION) AND SHARE

REPURCHASES ($4.4 BILLION). WE REPURCHASED 70 MILLION COMMON SHARES AT AN AVERAGE PRICE OF $63.11 IN 2016. THESE DIVIDEND AND SHARE REPURCHASE AMOUNTS COLLECTIVELY REPRESENT APPROXIMATELY 99 PERCENT OF TOTAL CAPITAL GENERATED DURING THE

YEAR.

